17 a valuable and vital public service to the state and to citizens and properties within the state
18 at a great personal sacrifice and risk to their own lives and well-being. The purpose of the
19 General Assembly, as provided for in this subpart, is to enable the authority to provide
20 educational grant assistance to the spouses and children of such persons who are killed or
21 permanently disabled in the line of duty."
22 SECTION 2.
23 Said subpart is further amended in Code Section 20-3-451, relating to definitions, by revising
24 paragraph (3) and by adding new paragraphs to read as follows:
25 "(2.1) 'Eligible student' means a person who qualifies for an educational grant under this
26 subpart.
27 (3) 'Firefighter' means a person employed, appointed, or regularly enrolled by the state
28 or by any county or municipal fire department whose duties include extinguishing fires
29 or investigating cases of suspected arson.
30 (3.1) 'In the line of duty' means:
31 (A) With respect to a volunteer firefighter, while on duty and when responding to or
32 returning from a fire or other emergency, performing duties during any fire or other
33 emergency, or performing duties intended to protect life and property, including,
34 without limitation, actual participation in a training exercise;
35 (B) With respect to a law enforcement officer or firefighter, while on duty and
36 performing services for and receiving compensation from the law enforcement or fire
37 service agency which employs such officer or firefighter, while off duty when
38 responding to any situation which would save a life or preserve the peace, or while
39 preventing or attempting to prevent the commission of a crime or fire; or
40 (C) With respect to a prison guard, while on duty and performing services for and
41 receiving compensation from the public agency which employs such prison guard."
