42 SECTION 3.
43 Said subpart is further amended by revising Code Section 20-3-453, relating to eligibility of
44 students, as follows:
45 "20-3-453.
46 No grants shall be payable to any person under this subpart who fails to meet any of the
47 following qualifications or restrictions:
48 (1) Such person must shall be the spouse or child, either natural or adopted, of a law
49 enforcement officer, firefighter, or prison guard who has been permanently disabled or
50 killed in the line of duty or while performing the duties to which he or she was assigned
51 in the normal course of employment. If such person is the adopted child of any such law
52 enforcement officer, firefighter, or prison guard, such person must shall have been
53 adopted and any final order of adoption issued prior to the date of the accident or event
54 causing the death or permanent disability of such parent;
55 (2) Such person must shall have been a citizen of this state for a period of at least 12
56 months immediately prior to the date of registration in an approved school and must shall
57 remain a citizen of the this state while receiving funds under this subpart;
58 (3) The deceased or disabled law enforcement officer, firefighter, or prison guard spouse
59 or parent of such person must shall have been an employee, either full-time or part-time,
60 or an officer or official, whether elected or appointed, of this state or any county,
61 municipality, department, board, bureau, branch, agency, commission, authority, or
62 political subdivision of the state on the date of the accident or event from which death or
63 permanent disability resulted; and
64 (4) Any person otherwise meeting the conditions of this subpart shall be eligible to
65 receive a grant even though the accident or the event causing the death or disability of
66 such person's spouse or parent occurred prior to July 1, 1980 2025."
