67 SECTION 4.
68 Said subpart is further amended by revising Code Section 20-3-455, relating to
69 administration of program and physical examinations, as follows:
70 "20-3-455.
71 The authority is authorized to prescribe such rules and regulations as may be necessary or
72 convenient for administration of this program and to establish procedures for determination
73 of eligibility of applicants. The authority is also authorized to establish standards and
74 procedures for verifying the death or permanent disability of the applicant's spouse or
75 parent and for such purpose is authorized to require a physical examination and to pay for
76 the cost of such examination from funds appropriated for use by the authority for the
77 purposes of this subpart."
78 SECTION 5.
79 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
